\section*{INSTITUTO DE FÍSICA FUNDAMENTAL}

Contacto del instituto: [ info.iff@iff.csic.es ]
Research groups:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Ab initio Simulations of Confined Molecular Systems and Photodissociation Dynamics (Abinifot)
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Our research is aimed at studying confined molecular systems via multiscale ab-initio modelling (e.g., supported metal clusters, helium nanodroplets, carbon nanotubes); and the dynamics of molecular photodissociation processes with the goal of controlling them by applying laser fields.

            \item Contacto
                \begin{itemize}
                    \item María Pilar de Lara Castells: [ Pilar.deLara.Castells@csic.es ]
                    \item Alberto García Vela: [ garciavela@iff.csic.es ]
                \end{itemize}
        \end{itemize}

    \item Astrophysics, Particle Physics and Cosmology (ASPARCOSMOS)

        La investigación de nuestro grupo abarca, por un lado, el estudio de la Energía Oscura, que es la causa desconocida de la expansión acelerada del Universo, junto con la física de las supernovas implicadas en las observaciones, confrontando así diversos tipos de modelos cosmológicos con estas. Por otro lado, investigamos varios problemas de la física teórica de las partículas elementales, incluyendo también la gravedad emergente y los fundamentos de la Mecánica Cuántica. Además, estamos visiblemente comprometidos con la divulgación científica, tanto impartiendo conferencias como escribiendo libros.

        Research lines and main objectives:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Observational and theoretical studies of Dark Energy.
            \item Theories of Modified Gravity
            \item Theories of Emergent Gravity
            \item The full development of Scan Quantum Mechanics
        \end{itemize}

        Contacto:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Pilar Ruiz Lapuente (Senior Scientist)
            \item Beatriz Gato Rivera (Senior Scientist)
            \item Pedro Martínez Gadea (Emeritus Scientist)
            \item Carlos García García (Ph.D. Student)
        \end{itemize}

    \item Molecular Astrophysics (ASTROMOL)

        El objetivo principal del Grupo de Astrofísica Molecular (GAM) del IFF-CSIC, es comprender la complejidad física y química en el medio circunestelar e interestelar desde un enfoque multidisciplinar e interdisciplinar, a través de la Astrofísica, la Química-Física teórica y experimental. la experimentación de laboratorio en condiciones de vacío, la Ciencia de Materiales, y la instrumentación astronómica para observatorios terrestres y en el espacio.

        Dichos entornos astrofísicos están regidos, principalmente, por moléculas en fase de gas y por granos de polvo y son completamente diferentes a la química que se da en condiciones terrestres. Nuestro objetivo es, en último extremo, intentar comprender cómo se forman las estrellas y los planetas.

        Contacto:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Javier R. Goicoechea (Group leader): [ javier.r.goicoechea@csic.es ]
            \item Octavio Roncero: [ Octavio.roncero@csic.es ]
            \item Pepe Cernicharo: [ jose.cernicharo@csic.es ]
        \end{itemize}

        Research lines and main objectives:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Detection of new molecules, Molecular Spectroscopy in Space and Laboratory Astrophysics
            \item Interstellar Medium, Photodissociation Regions and Far-Infrared Astrophysics
            \item Quantum Calculations of Molecular Processes in Astrophysics
            \item Chemical and Radiative Transfer Models
        \end{itemize}

    \item Theory and Simulation of Molecular Interactions (Intermol)

        Our research line focuses in building global and reliable intermolecular PESs and in the description of the nuclear motion on those PESs. We primarily follow a quantum-mechanical ab initio approach, although more approximated treatments are also used for the most complex systems. We intend a close exchange with experimental groups of the field. We aim to provide data (molecular properties, intermolecular potentials, collision rate coefficients) which are useful to other fields: astrochemistry, atmospheric, combustion or surface science etc., particularly for extreme or experimentally unaccesible conditions.

        Research topics:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Interacciones Moleculares en Oxígeno y Sistemas Relacionados
            \item Interacciones entre Gases Nobles y Materiales basados en Grafeno
            \item Propiedades moleculares y experimentos “in silica”
        \end{itemize}

        Contacto:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item José Campos Martínez: [ jcm@iff.csic.es ]
            \item Marta I. Hernández Hernández: [ marta@iff.csic.es ]
        \end{itemize}

    \item Molecular Clusters in Gas and Liquid Phases (MolClu)

        Our research group contributes in development of theoretical approaches, far beyond simplified models, and the design of specific computational tools to address efficiently real problems of physicochemical interest in the field that links science to technology and innovation. The main goal is the detailed understanding of a variety of molecular processes through quantum dynamics simulations. Our investigation focuses on the study of reactive collisions, large helium clusters doped with impurities, quantum molecular processes in nanoconfined systems and hydration effects in aqueous solutions. Our activities cooperate to build a proper environment for training young researchers and foster well-established collaborations ensuring progress in scientific knowledge/transfer.

        Contacto:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Salvador Miret Artés (Director del IFF): [ s.miret@iff.csic.es ]
            \item Tomás González Lezana: [ t.gonzalez.lezana@csic.es ]
        \end{itemize}

    \item Atomic and Molecular Processes of Biomedical Interest (RMI)

        Main objectives:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Analysis of the radiobiological effects of low energy electrons and molecular radicals
            \item Characterising potential molecular radiosensitizers
        \end{itemize}
        Contacto:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Gustavo García Gómez-Tejedor: [ g.garcia@csic.es ]
        \end{itemize}

    \item Quantum Information and Foundations Group (Quinfog)

        Research topics:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item Quantum Simulation
            \item Quantum and Quantum-Inspired Algorithms
            \item Quantum Optics and Photonics
            \item Quantum Computing Hardware
        \end{itemize}

        Contacto:
        \begin{itemize}
        \item \url{https://quinfog.hbar.es/contact/}
        \item Juan José García-Ripoll: [ jj.garcia.ripoll@csic.es ]
        \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

